name: millet production | millet | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/21663/documentation

This dataset represents the production of 1 kg of Pearl Millet during May-October, 2016 at a farm located in village Khokhar Kalan, District Mansa of Punjab State. The farm has a yield of 2625 kg fresh matter per ha for this crop cycle. Sowing date for the crop is 22-July, 2016 and harvesting date is 18-October, 2016. Mineral NP fertilizer input is 40-40 kg/ha. Machinery is used only for soil cultivation with fuel consumption of 19.03 kg/ha using plough for soil tillage and others.   

This activity starts about three weeks after the harvest of the previous crop. The soil is prepared for cultivation in first week of May and sowing of seeds started about eleven weeks after soil preparation. Thereafter the crop is mature for harvesting in about 2.5 months.

The activity ends with the harvesting of the mature Pearl millet plant
category: A:Agriculture, forestry and fishing/01:Crop and animal production, hunting and related service activities/011:Growing of non-perennial crops/0111:Growing of cereals (except rice), leguminous crops and oil seeds

processDocumentation.timeDescription: Soil cultivating date for the main crop: 04-May, 2016; Harvesting date main crop: 18-October, 2016. The soil cultivation, sowing and harvesting dates are taken as the middle date of the week or fortnight told to the data collector by the farmer. Total time from date of sowing to date of harvesting comes to 90 days.  The data is collected for one crop cycle. The cycle of one year is considered for entry in ecoeditor.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Cultivation of Pearl Millet follows conventional production standards
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: Ecoinvent LCI calculation tool for crop production was used to calculate field emissions from the cultivation process. Number of wet days and rainfall data is normal average for the district (Mansa) where the farm is located
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: The farmer was identified and contacted by agriculture science faculty familiar with the local farmers in the region. Data was collected directly from the farmer through semi-structured interview using a questionnaire based on the input requirements of the ecoinvent LCI calculation tool for crop production. The farmer does not maintain any written records and has provided the data from recent memory. In this region, typically farmers are unable to provide exact name of active ingredient in the pesticide they use and the same was noted from details given on the pesticide packet. Individual farmer is not able to calculate fuel consumption for his own farm alone and this information has been collected from farming community of the area.

'Country & land use unknown'. The emission are based on the relative change in production areas in all countries for a given crop.
